President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an Executive Order to take additional steps in response to the national emergency declared in Executive Order 14024, regarding the threat posed by harmful foreign activities of the Russian Federation. The order prohibits new investment in Russia by US persons, the exportation of certain services to persons in Russia, and any approval, financing, facilitation, or guarantee of a transaction by a US person that would be prohibited if performed by a US person or within the US. The full text of the Executive Order is enclosed with the report.